WEBVTT

00:03:29.442 --> 00:03:32.418
they can save lives from their couch.

00:03:32.990 --> 00:03:35.396
It's a new gig economy for volunteerism,

00:03:35.420 --> 00:03:38.610
like Uber or Lyft for volunteerism.

00:03:38.634 --> 00:03:40.555
And we also have full-time staff

00:03:40.579 --> 00:03:43.015
with a master's degree
in a relevant field.

00:03:43.039 --> 00:03:44.450
They're supervisors,

00:03:44.474 --> 00:03:48.149
and they watch every conversation
and step in if needed.

00:03:48.173 --> 00:03:50.109
Thanks to this technology and data

00:03:50.133 --> 00:03:52.291
and our volunteer labor model,

00:03:52.315 --> 00:03:55.045
we're able to reach
tons of people in pain.

00:03:55.069 --> 00:03:57.562
People who don't have access
to other resources,

00:03:57.586 --> 00:04:01.862
like the gay teenager
who can't share with his parents,